ective with a cross-cultural one, Ng's study represents a step forward in the study of Tokugawa intellectual history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAsian Studies : Asian Literature. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Japanese Studies. 4aHistory : Intellectual History. 7aHISTORY / Asia / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847308640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438473086423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438473086/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles